Rules:
- Generate at most {{ max_queries }} queries.
- Every query must be at most {{ max_query_length }} characters.
- Use the selected country, region, target language, source category, mission goal, and requested fields.
- Generate local-language terminology dynamically for the target country and language.
- For rehabilitation/addiction missions, include local equivalents of rehabilitation centre, addiction clinic, detox clinic, inpatient therapy, treatment centre, provider directory, and facility registry when relevant.
- Include both directory/registry queries and direct facility-page queries; do not spend all query slots on near-duplicate wording.
- Include an English query only when it materially improves discovery.
- Prefer official, regulator, ministry, licensing, accreditation, registry, or high-trust terms for official categories.
- Use region names separately when region scope is available.
- Do not hardcode Spain, Lebanon, or any other country-specific template.
- Do not use one English-only suffix for all missions.
- Do not generate URLs.
- Deduplicate query ideas before returning.

